race.comment: RHYTHM IS A DANCER (1) comes out of a strong rating contest when shouldering the 59.5kg for a fighting second over 1600m in the Coonabarabran Cup. Winning rider goes back on and doesn't have to improve much to win this. REMATCH (2) resumes after racing in much tougher grade last prep. Has a tidy first-up record and fitted with the two searching trials. Gets the dream run along the inside and regular rider hops back aboard. SHAMEDY (4) three weeks between runs when sitting on the pace for a tenacious fourth in the Coonabarabran Cup. Finding form at the right time and stays in the calculations. NIGHT FIGHTER (7) peaked fourth-up when back in class for a commanding victory over 1400m at Coonabarabran. Grima sticks but he doesn't get the same map favours here. Place best. THE HANGER CAT (3) quickly running out of chances after failing to deliver this prep. No excuses with the claim from the draw.
